### Fix ¬∑ Build ¬∑ CEP
- **Plugin install folder now uses ExtensionBundleId ‚Äî eliminates duplicate side-by-side installs** ‚Äî Prior to this fix the Electron app installed each CEP plugin to `%APPDATA%\Adobe\CEP\extensions\<sourceFolderName>\` (e.g. `SubMachine`, `MisterBloomX`), but the standalone `.bat` installers (`CEPs/SubMachine/Install_SubMachine.bat`, etc.) installed to `<ExtensionBundleId>` (e.g. `com.aescripts.submachine`, `com.bloomx.misterbloomx`). Result: a user who ran the `.bat` *and* `npm start` (or the installer .exe) ended up with two folders containing the same plugin, and Premiere would load both panels. Standardised every install path on the bundle id from `CSXS/manifest.xml`.
