## [v2.9.15] ‚Äî 2026-06-09

### Fix ¬∑ Audio ¬∑ CEP ¬∑ Logic
- **Timeline clip name still showed dummy after project item rename** ‚Äî Premiere Pro does not propagate a project item rename to already-placed timeline clips. After `target.name = newName` in `doReplaceInPremiere`, an ExtendScript loop now iterates all sequences, both audio and video tracks, and sets `clip.name = newName` for any clip whose current name still matches `dName`. (`cep-extension/audio.js`)
- **Stale empty-file cache served after broken render** ‚Äî `process_audio` cache check only tested `fs.existsSync(outPath)`. Prior broken renders (caused by the `-to 0` FFmpeg bug) produced 44-byte files containing only the WAV header. These were being served as valid audio, causing the `changeMediaPath` call to fail silently. Fixed by also requiring `fs.statSync(outPath).size > 44`. (`main.js`)
- **Option C slot map missing bin names** ‚Äî The first-drop Option C slot map only wrote `folder` entries; `bin` was always `null`, so `process_audio` routed all imports to the root Premiere bin. Fixed: derive bin names from `fileTpl.bins_json` using `inferSlotType` and explicit `slotType`/`slotTypes` fields, matching normal project-creation bin derivation. (`main.js`)
- **`process_audio` couldn't locate Option C slot map** ‚Äî Handler only looked in `path.dirname(resolvedProjectPath)` (the `.prproj` folder), not in the dated folder under `appConfig.targetDir`. Added an Option C detection block: if normal slot map lookup yields nothing and `targetDir` is set, reconstruct today's dated folder path and load the slot map from there. (`main.js`)

